            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">43.201</ph> General.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d2566e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2580e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Generally, Government contracts contain a changes clause that permits the contracting officer to make unilateral changes, in designated areas, within the general scope of the contract. These are accomplished by issuing written change orders on <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/amendment-solicitationmodification-contract"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">Standard Form 30</xref>, Amendment of Solicitation/Modification of Contract (<xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/amendment-solicitationmodification-contract"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">SF 30</xref>), unless otherwise provided (see <xref href="FAR-i1073804.dita#i1073804"
                        base="i1073804"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">43.301</xref>).</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2580e35" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contractor must continue performance of the contract as changed, except that in cost-reimbursement or incrementally funded contracts the contractor is not obligated to continue performance or incur costs beyond the limits established in the Limitation of Cost or Limitation of Funds clause (see <xref href="FAR-i1081712.dita#i1081712"
                        base="i1081712"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">32.706-2</xref>).</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2580e47" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contracting officer may issue a change order by electronic means without a <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/amendment-solicitationmodification-contract"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">SF 30</xref> under unusual or urgent circumstances, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">provided</i> that the message contains substantially the information required by the <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/amendment-solicitationmodification-contract"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">SF 30</xref> and immediate action is taken to issue the <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/amendment-solicitationmodification-contract"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">SF 30</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
